      "Impeding further travel to the east is a wall of tremendous boulders, a barricade to the immense summit that imposes a foreboding shadow over an already darkened trail.  Freshly cut limbs and branches rest in an orderly pile beneath a covered stand filled with a variety of pruning tools and other miscellaneous items.  Just beyond a wide crevice in the ground, a rock-spattered ledge clings to the mountain face and wends back and forth toward a moderate clearing set back from the trail's sharp edge."
